   1:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c **** /**
   2:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   ******************************************************************************
   3:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @file    system_stm32f4xx.c
   4:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @author  MCD Application Team
   5:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @version V1.8.1
   6:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @date    27-January-2022
   7:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @brief   CMSIS Cortex-M4 Device Peripheral Access Layer System Source File.
   8:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *          This file contains the system clock configuration for STM32F4xx devices.
   9:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             
  10:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * 1.  This file provides two functions and one global variable to be called from 
  11:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *     user application:
  12:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *      - SystemInit(): Setups the system clock (System clock source, PLL Multiplier
  13:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                      and Divider factors, AHB/APBx prescalers and Flash settings),
  14:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                      depending on the configuration made in the clock xls tool. 
  15:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                      This function is called at startup just after reset and 
  16:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                      before branch to main program. This call is made inside
  17:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                      the "startup_stm32f4xx.s" file.
  18:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *
  19:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClock variable: Contains the core clock (HCLK), it can be used
  20:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                  by the user application to setup the SysTick 
  21:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                  timer or configure other parameters.
  22:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                     
  23:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClockUpdate(): Updates the variable SystemCoreClock and must
  24:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                 be called whenever the core clock is changed
  25:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                 during program execution.
  26:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *
  27:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * 2. After each device reset the HSI (16 MHz) is used as system clock source.
  28:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    Then SystemInit() function is called, in "startup_stm32f4xx.s" file, to
  29:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    configure the system clock before to branch to main program.
  30:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *
  31:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * 3. If the system clock source selected by user fails to startup, the SystemInit()
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc2bu7Wx.s 			page 2


  32:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    function will do nothing and HSI still used as system clock source. User can 
  33:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    add some code to deal with this issue inside the SetSysClock() function.
  34:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *
  35:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * 4. The default value of HSE crystal is set to 25MHz, refer to "HSE_VALUE" define
  36:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    in "stm32f4xx.h" file. When HSE is used as system clock source, directly or
  37:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    through PLL, and you are using different crystal you have to adapt the HSE
  38:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    value to your own configuration.
  39:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *
  40:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * 5. This file configures the system clock as follows:
  41:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *=============================================================================
  42:CMSIS/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *=============================================================================
